######FILE/GROUP OWNERSHIP:

#to change the owner of the file
sudo chown newowner_username filename

eg. touch file1 file2
sudo chown xyz file1

#to change the owner group of the file
sudo chgrp newowner_groupname filename
eg. sudo chgrp bigdata file1

#to change both user and group owner simultaneously
sudo chown newowneruser:newownergroup filename
eg. sudo chown bigdata:bigdata file1

######FILE PERMISSIONS:
sudo chmod u+x filename
sudo chmod ugo+w filename
sudo chmod a+x filename
sudo chmod u+rwx,g+rx,o-w filename
sudo chmod 674 filename
sudo chmod 000 filename
sudo chmod â€“R 777 filename/dirname

/etc/passwd file has list of all users (system users & human users) created.
/etc/group has list of all groups
